ho work in the medical arena need to take a step back and check your crap at the door.<br><br>The advances made in medicine have been significant since the late 1800's. But that doesn't mean we have the ability to make everything better for every person. Maybe in another 100 years, we might, but today we do not. The world we live isn't like Star trek where some little piece of equipment can diagnose and treat any known ailment. This is the real world, where people still die from things like pneumonia. <br><br>Yes, misdiagnosis still happens. No, medical professionals can not cure every ailment out there. However, we have come much further than we were even 20 years ago. Feel LUCKY you live in today's day and age vice 100 years ago, or more. Instead of bagging on those who practice medicine and spend their days trying as HARD AS THEY CAN to make people better, why don't you give them props? That, or try and become a doctor yourself and research cures for all known ailments....then tell everyone how easy that profession is. <br><br>Trust me, doctors feel like SHIT when they miss something or do something that hurts a patient. Understand, they are human! And by being human they are not perfect. As much as medical professionals WISH and TRY to be perfect, they are not.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#E5E5E6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub110.ezboard.com/umonocot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>monocot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Cyber Pimp</span><br> <font color=#000033>(6/4/02 4:52:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub110.ezboard.com/feqasylumrantsandravesbalancingissues.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2562.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Medical Profession today..</span><hr size=1> Ole said:<br>In my experience, most surgeons are not made of gold.<br><br>Instead they are made of ego and greed. <br><br>I have to actually 